{
  "stem": "3341.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So they-- the overseas-- they-- half of them were usually from other countries, overseas visitors, because the textile industry was very important all over Europe.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So you had to have good connections to get a child to this sort of academy.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But what they didn't know, or-- or didn't want to know, when-- when my-- the friend of my father enrolled me in the textile academy, there were two, because they-- the school was established 1740 or '50.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was originally a German school.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But when Czechoslovakia was established-- that was in 1918-- the state arranged and they started was the textile academy in Czech.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That was the language of the country.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the better school was the historical one, which was a German.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And naturally, a Jewish friend of my father-- they spoke German at home.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He was-- you see, many Jewish people in our country were either German-minded or Hungarian, or something in between which developed only later as Czechoslovakian.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 55,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I belonged culturally to the Czechoslovakian-minded group.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 56,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But he was German-minded.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And he was German-minded.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My name was originally Hirschmann, which is a typical German name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So naturally, he enrolled me in a German school.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when I arrived there, that was the first shock, the first surprise, because I understood German, but I spoke very, very little of it.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We spoke at home Slovak.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Even now, with my dear wife, I speak Slovak because that is my mother language.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 57,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And that was the shock for me because when I entered the classroom and I faced professors-- and the German section of the textile academy was on a very high standard.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
